>[Question]
>Hi!Dr. Math
>   When I learned Geometry n-spaces,I saw the equation of plane:
>     x/(a)+y/(b)+z/(c)=1
>   I know a(b,c) stands for the intercept,however,I feel strange 
>which magic makes x/(a)+y/(b)+z/(c) equal 1 on the beam? So I regard 
>x/(a) as a whole and want to know its Geometry interpretion.In other 
>words,How can I guess the result from figure?
>   Could you give me a hand?
>mathew 
>      
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
